Paper: hep-th/9902178

Date: 1999-02-24

Title: A Note on the Superstring BRST Operator

Authors: J.N. Acosta, N. Berkovits and O. Chandia (IFT/UNESP, Sao Paulo)

Comments: 4 pages latex

Journal-ref: Phys.Lett. B454 (1999) 247-248

We write the BRST operator of the N=1 superstring as $Q= e^{-R} (\oint dz\gamma^2 b)e^R$ where $\gamma$ and $b$ are super-reparameterization ghosts.This provides a trivial proof that $Q$ is nilpotent.